    "The absolute feature span divided by F D is the relative feature span.",
    "A higher feature span most likely results from a higher disagreement amongst methods.",
    "Consequently, the user will be able to choose many features as part of the explanation.",
    "The maximum relative feature span of 1 is achieved when every single feature is used in at least one explanation.",
    "These relative feature spans are shown in Tables 7 and 8: If we revisit the example of Sect. 3.1 and assume that the user only has the first two counterfactual explanation algorithms, CFproto and WIT, available."
